Package: moreutils
Version: 0.69-r2
Depends: libc, perl, perlbase-file, perlbase-getopt, perlbase-io, perlbase-ipc, perlbase-posix, perlbase-time
Source: feeds/packages/utils/moreutils
SourceName: moreutils
License: GPL-2.0-or-later
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Section: utils
SourceDateEpoch: 1761595978
URL: https://joeyh.name/code/moreutils/
Maintainer: Nikil Mehta <nikil.mehta@gmail.com>
Architecture: mipsel_24kc
Installed-Size: 634880
Filename: moreutils_0.69-r2_mipsel_24kc.ipk
Size: 34116
SHA256sum: 19db496686bb64091afd6aa7d07258963d2e30d43cd8d09ff73b9557786f23f5
Description:  This is a growing collection of the Unix tools that nobody thought
 to write long ago, when Unix was young.
 .
 So far, it includes the following utilities:
 - chronic: runs a command quietly unless it fails
 - combine: combine the lines in two files using boolean operations
 - errno: look up errno names and descriptions
 - ifdata: get network interface info without parsing ifconfig output
 - ifne: run a program if the standard input is not empty
 - isutf8: check if a file or standard input is utf-8
 - lckdo: execute a program with a lock held
 - mispipe: pipe two commands, returning the exit status of the first
 - parallel: run multiple jobs at once
 - pee: tee standard input to pipes
 - sponge: soak up standard input and write to a file
 - ts: timestamp standard input
 - vidir: edit a directory in your text editor
 - vipe: insert a text editor into a pipe
 - zrun: automatically uncompress arguments to command

